JOHANNESBURG - In the past 24 hours, 7,657 COVID-19 infections have been reported in South Africa, pushing the country's overall caseload to about 1,747,000. Fifty-nine additional COVID-19 deaths have been recorded to the country's death toll in the same 24-hour cycle, bringing the total number of fatalities to 57,765. So far, 1,606,000 people have recovered from the virus. According to the Health Department, 1,773,000 vaccines have been administered for people aged 60 and above as well as healthcare workers. 13 June 2021 #COVID19 statistics in South Africa #CoronaVirusSA      https://t.co/1yZ0fxDYvk  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.